		</header>
		<section>					
			<h2 id="build-responsive-fluid-web-with-confidence">Build Responsive Fluid Web with Confidence</h2>
			<p>ClampGenerator is a modern, developer-first tool to create responsive, fluid typography and layout spacing using CSS <code>clamp()</code>. It's built by the team at <strong>NViews Web</strong>‚Äîthe same creators of <a href="https://clampcalculator.com/">ClampCalculator.com</a>.</p>
			<p>Unlike simple calculators, ClampGenerator goes further: live previews, design-to-code output, typescale customization, and layout spacing utilities‚Äîall production-ready.</p>
			<h2 id="why-we-created-clampgenerator">Why We Created ClampGenerator</h2>
			<p>While developing client projects at NViews Web, we needed tools that offered:</p>
			<ul>
			<li>Real-time responsive typography preview  </li>
			<li>Custom multipliers per element (h1-h6, small, code)  </li>
			<li>Layout spacing clamp (margin, padding, gap)  </li>
			<li>Plain CSS, Tailwind, or SCSS output  </li>
			<li>Offline-ready performance without logins</li>
			</ul>
			<p>Existing clamp tools fell short. So, we built our own.</p>
			<h2 id="mission">Mission</h2>
			<p>Our goal is to <strong>simplify modern responsive design</strong> by handling the math, slope logic, and scaling.</p>
			<p>Focus on creativity. We handle the clamp().</p>
			<p>ClampGenerator empowers developers and designers to:</p>
			<ul>
			<li>Skip manual <code>clamp()</code> math  </li>
			<li>Maintain consistent typescales  </li>
			<li>Scale layouts without breakpoints</li>
			</ul>
